Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.59,1:33:22.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,他提到雅加达了吗\N{\rENG}Did he mention Jakarta?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.21,1:33:24.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,我等会再联系你\N{\rENG}I'll call you back.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.17,1:33:30.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,纽约证券交易所刚刚暂停了交易\N{\rENG}The New York Stock Exchange just suspended trading.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.26,1:33:33.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们把瓦肖矿业停牌了\N{\rENG}They've taken Washoe off the board.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.24,1:33:48.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,你卖了一些吧\N{\rENG}You sold some, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.36,1:33:49.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.74,1:33:52.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rENG}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.20,1:33:53.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,鲍勃\N{\rENG}Bobby
Dialogue: 0,1:33:53.87,1:33:55.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,我以为\N{\rENG}I thought...
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.00,1:33:58.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,股价只会一直攀升\N{\rENG}I thought it was just gonna keep going up.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.04,1:34:01.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,真是的 鲍勃 我早就告诉你\N{\rENG}Damn it, Bobby, I told you from the beginning
Dialogue: 0,1:34:01.67,1:34:04.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,卖掉一些股票存点钱以防万一\N{\rENG}just put some away, save a little bit just in case.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.46,1:34:06.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我跟你说过多少次了\N{\rENG}How many times did I tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.46,1:34:07.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯尼 你早就知道吗\N{\rENG}Kenny, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:07.88,1:34:09.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,你早就知道吗\N{\rENG}Did you know, Kenny?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.72,1:34:11.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我早就知道吗\N{\rENG}Did I know?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.51,1:34:15.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,你竟然问我这个问题\N{\rENG}I can't believe you would ask me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.43,1:34:17.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,我就问你 你早就知道吗\N{\rENG}I'm asking you that. Did you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.27,1:34:18.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,不 我不知道 鲍勃\N{\rENG}No, I goddamn didn't know, Bobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.48,1:34:22.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯尼\N{\rENG}Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.86,1:34:26.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 肯尼  - 什么\N{\rENG}- Kenny.  - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.98,1:34:28.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,这话不知从何说起\N{\rENG}I don't even know how to tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:28.11,1:34:29.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,你自己看吧\N{\rENG}Just look.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.70,1:34:35.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿科斯塔抛售了他的股票\N{\rENG}Acosta was dumping stock.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.58,1:34:37.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗯  - 空壳公司\N{\rENG}- Mm.  - Shell companies.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:37.20,1:34:39.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,在菲律宾 亚速尔群岛\N{\rENG}Banks in the Philippines, the fucking Azores.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.62,1:34:40.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,和直布罗陀的银行\N{\rENG}Gibraltar.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.75,1:34:42.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,多种机构 都是海外的\N{\rENG}Multiple layers, all offshore.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.88,1:34:46.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,多少\N{\rENG}How much?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.59,1:34:49.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,一点六四亿\N{\rENG}$164 million.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.97,1:34:53.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\rENG}Okay, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:34:53.59,1:34:55.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们怎么办\N{\rENG}what are we gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.02,1:35:03.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真不敢相信\N{\rENG}I don't fucking believe this. Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.61,1:35:07.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们是FBI\N{\rENG}This is the FBI!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:08.03,1:35:10.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,离开你们的办公桌\N{\rENG}Step away from your desks!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.44,1:35:13.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,离开你们的办公桌两大步\N{\rENG}Take two big steps away from your desks!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:13.49,1:35:15.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要触碰任何东西\N{\rENG}Do not touch anything!
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.17,1:35:34.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在这一诈骗中损失了多少钱\N{\rENG\i1}How much money was lost in the fraud,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:34.55,1:35:36.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我们所知的  - 数十亿\N{\rENG}- that we know of?  - Oh, billions.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:36.51,1:35:37.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,光是大机构投资者\N{\rENG}Large institutional investors
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.06,1:35:39.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 就损失了数十亿美元  - 所以这个…\N{\rENG}- lost billions of dollars.  - So one
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.06,1:35:41.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那么他们一两个人\N{\rENG\i1}or maybe both of them,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.64,1:35:45.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就把华尔街的人都骗了？\N{\rENG\i1}two outsiders, took everybody on Wall Street for a ride?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:46.11,1:35:47.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}是这样的\N{\rENG\i1}Yeah, it really looks like they did.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.52,1:35:49.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的  - 阿科斯塔己经失踪了？\N{\rENG}- Yeah.  - And Acosta has vanished?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.90,1:35:52.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,带着上亿美元\N{\rENG}With hundreds of millions of dollars.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.65,1:35:55.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯尼・威尔斯一直声称自己是无辜的\N{\rENG}Kenny Wells has always maintained his innocence,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:56.12,1:35:58.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}和别人一样被骗了\N{\rENG\i1}that he was duped along with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.91,1:36:01.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}鉴于这一点 你怎么看待此事\N{\rENG\i1}Given that, what do you make of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.08,1:36:07.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯尼・威尔斯 傻瓜还是主谋？\N{\rENG}Kenny Wells, a fool or a mastermind?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.71,1:36:12.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}这是个很好的问题 罗杰\N{\rENG\i1}It's a <i>very good question, Roger.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:32.36,1:36:33.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃\N{\rENG}Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.11,1:36:40.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,迈克・阿科斯塔是我的朋友和合伙人\N{\rENG}Mike-Mike Acosta was my friend and, uh, my partner.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:40.58,1:36:41.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,呃\N{\rENG}Um...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.16,1:36:46.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,他背叛了我\N{\rENG}and he-he betrayed me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:46.12,1:36:49.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道身为瓦肖矿业公司总栽\N{\rENG}I-I know as CEO of Washoe Mining
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.79,1:36:51.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,我有责任知道\N{\rENG}it's my responsibility to know
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.05,1:36:54.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,发生的一切可我不知道\N{\rENG}everything that's going on, and I... I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.22,1:36:58.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不是借口\N{\rENG}It's not an excuse.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.51,1:37:00.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真诚地向大家道歉\N{\rENG}All right? I sincerely apologize
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.51,1:37:04.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,任何在投资中遭受损失的人\N{\rENG}to everybody and anybody that lost on their investments.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.35,1:37:09.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,迈克\N{\rENG}Come on, Mike.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:10.06,1:37:12.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,快回来吧\N{\rENG}Mikey, come on in, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.19,1:37:14.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吗\N{\rENG}All right?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.03,1:37:16.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是怎么回事\N{\rENG}What happened, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:33.92,1:37:36.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 霍华德  - 我在电视上看到了你\N{\rENG}- Howard.  - I saw you on TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.26,1:37:39.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我能和你谈一会吗  - 抱歉\N{\rENG}- Hey, man, can I talk to you for a minute, please?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:39.30,1:37:41.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只想知道我的钱去了哪里\N{\rENG}Look, I just want to know where my money went.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.30,1:37:43.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 拜托 我一无所知  - 威尔斯先生\N{\rENG}- Come on! Don't know anything about it, okay?  - Mr. Wells,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:43.39,1:37:46.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,威尔斯先生 你什么时候退房\N{\rENG}Mr. Wells, exactly when will you be departing?
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.35,1:37:49.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,一两天后吧 我会告诉你的\N{\rENG}Uh, later. A few days or so. I'll let you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:49.31,1:37:52.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我只想谈谈你的账单  - 我等会下来\N{\rENG}- We just need to talk about your bill, sir.  - I'll be down.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.19,1:37:53.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,把这事解决\N{\rENG}We'll settle it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.76,1:39:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要律师吗\N{\rENG}Do I need a lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.97,1:39:03.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你需要吗\N{\rENG}Do you need a lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:06.76,1:39:08.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就对了\N{\rENG}Right answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.74,1:39:22.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你是怎么见到迈克・阿科斯塔的\N{\rENG\i1}How'd you meet Michael Acosta?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.99,1:39:29.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,第一次还是第二次？\N{\rENG}The, uh, first time or the second time?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.41,1:39:31.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,你怎么见到他的 威尔斯\N{\rENG}How'd you meet him, Wells?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.75,1:39:36.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,当时是一九八八年四月\N{\rENG}It was April... of '88.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.55,1:39:40.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,那时我干劲很足\N{\rENG}Yeah, I was on the balls of my ass.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.84,1:39:43.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,瞎忙活\N{\rENG}Scrambling.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.63,1:39:46.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,虽然对我来说并非未知的领域\N{\rENG}Not exactly uncharted waters for me, but...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.93,1:39:49.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我陷得很深\N{\rENG}I was in deep.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:57.36,1:39:59.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想你不大可能\N{\rENG}I think it's pretty unlikely
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.15,1:40:01.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,再次见到你的合伙人了\N{\rENG}we'll ever see your partner again.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.70,1:40:06.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 为何这么说  - 很多有权有势的人\N{\rENG}- What are you talking about?  - A lot of very powerful people
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.28,1:40:08.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,都对迈克・阿科斯塔很愤怒\N{\rENG}are very angry at Michael Acosta.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.20,1:40:13.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,发生了什么\N{\rENG}Well, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:13.83,1:40:14.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,发生了什么？\N{\rENG}What happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:40:15.00,1:40:17.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,一百七十亿美元的价值一夜之间消失\N{\rENG}$17 billion of value disappeared overnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:17.79,1:40:19.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,迈克・阿科斯塔在楼下的舞厅\N{\rENG}Mike Acosta waves good-bye to you
Dialogue: 0,1:40:19.24,1:40:21.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,中与你道别乘坐包机\N{\rENG}in the ballroom downstairs and goes back to Indonesia
Dialogue: 0,1:40:21.46,1:40:23.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}带着瓦肖基金返回了印尼\N{\rENG\i1}on a jet chartered with Washoe funds.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.97,1:40:26.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然后他失踪了\N{\rENG\i1}And then he does a disappearing act.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.84,1:40:28.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但这事你知道\N{\rENG\i1}But this you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:29.05,1:40:32.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他先是被内政部长禁止进入\N{\rENG\i1}First, he's locked out of the assay lab in Kalimantan
Dialogue: 0,1:40:32.52,1:40:34.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}加里曼丹的化验室\N{\rENG\i1}by the minister of the interior.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.06,1:40:36.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 于是他回到雅加达  - 阿科斯塔先生\N{\rENG}- <i>So he goes back to Jakarta...  - Mr. Acosta,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.98,1:40:38.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,请跟我走一趟\N{\rENG}please walk with with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:38.48,1:40:40.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他在机场\N{\rENG\i1}Where he's immediately detained
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.48,1:40:42.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}立刻被印尼军方拘留\N{\rENG\i1}by the Indonesian military.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.11,1:40:45.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们控制了他\N{\rENG\i1}And they hold him
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.61,1:40:47.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}试图重现瓦肖公司声称的\N{\rENG\i1}while they try to reproduce for themselves
Dialogue: 0,1:40:47.82,1:40:50.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}样品化验结果\N{\rENG\i1}the lab results claimed by Washoe.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.79,1:40:54.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,当然 他们无法做到\N{\rENG}Which, of course, they are unable to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:54.75,1:40:57.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,在这时\N{\rENG}Now, at this point,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.50,1:41:00.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,他要么正被转移到监狱关押\N{\rENG}either he's being transferred to an actual prison, or...
Dialogue: 0,1:41:00.63,1:41:02.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,要么他贿赂了某个官员\N{\rENG}he's bribed one of the officers.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.55,1:41:03.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,反正\N{\rENG}Either way,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.67,1:41:05.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他上了一架军用直升机\N{\rENG\i1}he's on a military helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.09,1:41:10.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}向北飞行大致沿着Kensana\N{\rENG\i1}They fly north, loosely tracking the Kensana River.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.68,1:42:01.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一千英尺的高空在Kensana上方\N{\rENG\i1}A thousand feet up, over the Kensana...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.94,1:42:04.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}迈克・阿科斯塔一头摔了下去\N{\rENG\i1}Mike Acosta takes a header.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.04,1:42:17.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,不可能\N{\rENG}No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:17.91,1:42:20.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,绝不可能\N{\rENG}No fucking way.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:20.75,1:42:22.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,这要么是他装死\N{\rENG}He either faked it,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:22.67,1:42:24.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,要么是他花钱请人\N{\rENG}or he paid to have this-this bullshit story
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.92,1:42:26.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,把这件事报道出来\N{\rENG}you're telling put out.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:26.59,1:42:30.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,一点六四亿美元在印尼能办成很多事情\N{\rENG}$164 million goes a long way in Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:30.93,1:42:33.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,他们发现了一具尸体\N{\rENG}They found a body.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.86,1:42:51.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}手和脸被吃掉了\N{\rENG\i1}Hands and face were eaten away,
Dialogue: 0,1:42:51.36,1:42:54.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}可能是野猪\N{\rENG\i1}probably by wild pigs.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:54.41,1:42:56.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你确定是他吗\N{\rENG}Sure this is him?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:57.08,1:42:59.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,我什么都不确定\N{\rENG}I'm not sure of anything...
Dialogue: 0,1:42:59.54,1:43:04.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只知道迈克・阿科斯塔用滤水器换取河金\N{\rENG\i1}except Mike Acosta traded water filters for river gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:04.38,1:43:05.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但现在印尼政府\N{\rENG\i1}But now the Indonesian government
Dialogue: 0,1:43:06.04,1:43:07.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}对这件事\N{\rENG\i1}have gone unusually quiet
Dialogue: 0,1:43:07.46,1:43:09.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,异常的保持沉默\N{\rENG}on the subject.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.26,1:43:10.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,做过一次尸体解剖\N{\rENG}There was an autopsy
Dialogue: 0,1:43:10.97,1:43:12.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,证实了死者的身份\N{\rENG}corroborating the identity of the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:14.30,1:43:16.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他们然后封了报告\N{\rENG\i1}They then sealed the report...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:18.56,1:43:20.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,火化了遗体\N{\rENG}cremated the remains.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.73,1:43:25.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,有意思的是 你的朋友丹尼・苏哈托\N{\rENG}Interestingly, Danny Suharto, your friend...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:25.27,1:43:28.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,也抛售了很多股票\N{\rENG}dumped a lot of stock as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:28.28,1:43:31.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以现在苏哈托家族更富有了\N{\rENG}So the Suhartos are even richer now.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:31.24,1:43:34.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,迈克・阿科斯塔表面上己经死了下葬了\N{\rENG}Mike Acosta is ostensibly dead and buried, and...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:34.70,1:43:36.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,一点六四亿美元依然下落不明\N{\rENG}$164 million is still missing.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:37.12,1:43:40.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,如今我剩下的\N{\rENG}And the only question...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:40.62,1:43:42.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,唯一的问题是\N{\rENG}I'm left with is...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.92,1:43:45.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,这事你是否参与其中\N{\rENG}whether or not you were in on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:47.59,1:43:49.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,我\N{\rENG}I...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:49.92,1:43:53.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我不信  - 不信什么\N{\rENG}- I can't believe it.  - Can't believe what?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:53.38,1:43:56.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,这一行业\N{\rENG}No, look, th-this business...
Dialogue: 0,1:43:57.10,1:43:59.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,几年前就把迈克淘汰了\N{\rENG}had written Mike off years ago, all right?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.77,1:44:01.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,说他的理论是一佗屎\N{\rENG}They called his theories crap.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:01.31,1:44:03.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,不过\N{\rENG}But...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.31,1:44:05.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,这不可能\N{\rENG}there's no way.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:05.27,1:44:07.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不可能\N{\rENG}He wouldn't, he fucking couldn't
Dialogue: 0,1:44:07.31,1:44:09.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,希望身后是这样的名声\N{\rENG}let this be the last word on him.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:09.57,1:44:13.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 这不可能  - 你指的是阿科斯塔还是你自己\N{\rENG}- No fucking way.  - You talking about Acosta or yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:23.00,1:44:26.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,听着 我们当时钱快花光了\N{\rENG}All right, look. We-we-we were running out of money, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:26.67,1:44:29.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,疟疾也让我奄奄一息了\N{\rENG}And I was practically dying from malaria.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:29.34,1:44:31.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,我把我名下最后的钱都给了迈克\N{\rENG}I gave Mike the last dollar to my name.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.09,1:44:34.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,让他对我做个承诺我说：迈克\N{\rENG}And I made him promise me something, I said, "Mike...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:34.88,1:44:38.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,别让我一无所获的死去\N{\rENG}don't let me die out here for nothing."
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.35,1:44:46.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,几周后我苏醒过来\N{\rENG}A few weeks later, I came to, and...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.44,1:44:48.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,迈克就在旁边\N{\rENG}Mike was there.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:52.03,1:44:54.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,他说：\N{\rENG}He said, "We got...
Dialogue: 0,1:44:54.19,1:44:56.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们找到了肯尼\N{\rENG}"we got a strike, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.66,1:44:59.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们找到了金矿\N{\rENG}We got a goddamn gold mine."
Dialogue: 0,1:45:04.54,1:45:09.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不可能是为了欺骗所有人\N{\rENG}And th-there's no way that he set out to swindle anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.58,1:45:12.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,他只是多需要点时问\N{\rENG}He just needed to buy a little more time.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.34,1:45:19.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,他不想让我失望\N{\rENG}And he didn't want to let me down.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:19.51,1:45:23.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你撒谎  - 莱文 坐下\N{\rENG}- You're fuckin' lyin'.  - Levine, sit down!
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.43,1:45:25.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想谈谈真相吗\N{\rENG}You want to talk about the truth?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:25.35,1:45:26.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧我们谈谈真相\N{\rENG}All right, let's talk about the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.02,1:45:29.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,唯一的真相是 只要能发财\N{\rENG}The only truth here is, when everybody's getting rich,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.27,1:45:32.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,没人在乎真相是什么\N{\rENG}nobody gives a shit about the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:32.19,1:45:35.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,拜托人们只需要仔细看看\N{\rENG}Come the fuck on. All anyone had to do was look,
Dialogue: 0,1:45:35.40,1:45:37.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,睁开眼看看\N{\rENG}open their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.24,1:45:40.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,样品中的金子是错的金矿储量又过于巨大\N{\rENG}Man, the-the gold was wrong, the find was too good.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:40.45,1:45:43.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,有太多的疑点\N{\rENG}There were red flags everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:43.12,1:45:44.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,为什么没人仔细看\N{\rENG}Why did no one look?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.87,1:45:46.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为没人想知道\N{\rENG}'Cause no one wanted to fucking know.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:46.96,1:45:48.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们都愿意相信\N{\rENG}We all wanted to believe.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:48.96,1:45:50.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,你 我 所有人 为什么呢\N{\rENG}Me, you, fucking everybody. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.38,1:45:55.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我们都能发大财\N{\rENG}Because we were all making so much fucking money, man.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.76,1:45:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,这就是真相\N{\rENG}That's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:58.18,1:46:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,千百年来一直如此\N{\rENG}That's been going on for fucking centuries!
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.51,1:46:05.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,天\N{\rENG}Oh, fuck...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:08.73,1:46:11.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道迈克・阿科斯塔\N{\rENG}Were you aware Mike Acosta was salting
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.40,1:46:13.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 在样品中撒金子吗  - 不知道\N{\rENG}- the Washoe core samples?  - No.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.94,1:46:15.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不知道\N{\rENG}You had no knowledge
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.48,1:46:18.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}迈克・阿科斯塔在搞诈骗？\N{\rENG\i1}Mike Acosta was perpetrating a fraud?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:18.45,1:46:20.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- 不知道  - 在Kensana金矿一事上\N{\rENG\i1}- No.  - You were not in collusion
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.95,1:46:23.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你不是迈克・阿科斯塔的同谋？\N{\rENG\i1}with Mike Acosta on the Kensana gold strike?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.95,1:46:27.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,不是 我还以为中了大奖\N{\rENG}No, man, I fucking thought I won the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.95,1:46:31.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,你从诈骗案中获利了吗\N{\rENG}Did you profit from the Kensana fraud?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:33.71,1:46:36.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 没有  - 你有亲友获利吗\N{\rENG}- No.  - Did anyone close to you profit?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:37.84,1:46:40.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的朋友们损失了钱\N{\rENG}My friends lost money.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:40.55,1:46:42.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的邻居损失了钱\N{\rENG}My neighbors lost money.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:42.51,1:46:44.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,而我\N{\rENG}Me...
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.68,1:46:47.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,失去了一切\N{\rENG}I lost everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:50.14,1:46:52.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,说实话\N{\rENG}You know what the truth of it is?
Dialogue: 0,1:46:54.06,1:46:56.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在乎的并不是钱\N{\rENG}I never really cared about money.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.28,1:46:59.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在乎的是金子\N{\rENG}I cared about gold.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.95,1:47:02.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,这是两码事 詹宁斯\N{\rENG}And it's different, Jennings.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.24,1:47:04.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,完全是两码事\N{\rENG}It's fucking different.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.34,1:47:26.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,对肯尼・威尔斯的审查结束\N{\rENG}Interview terminated with Kenny Wells...
Dialogue: 0,1:47:26.81,1:47:29.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,上午六点四十五\N{\rENG}6:45 a.m.,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:29.89,1:47:33.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,一九八八年十月十七日\N{\rENG}October 17, 1988.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:33.52,1:47:34.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,审问者是我\N{\rENG}Interview conducted by myself,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:34.94,1:47:37.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,保罗・詹宁斯特工\N{\rENG}Paul K. Jennings, special agent.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.23,1:47:40.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,也代表莱文和班克斯特工\N{\rENG}Also present, agents Levine and Banks,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.53,1:47:42.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,联邦调查局\N{\rENG}Federal Bureau of Investigation,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:42.53,1:47:44.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,内华达州 里诺\N{\rENG}district of Nevada, Reno.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:56.63,1:47:58.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,肯尼・威尔斯先生\N{\rENG}Mr. Kenny Wells...
Dialogue: 0,1:48:01.63,1:48:03.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,你可以走了\N{\rENG}you are free to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.59,1:48:08.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,看啊\N{\rENG}Well, lookee there.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.60,1:48:10.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,有人相信我\N{\rENG}Somebody believes me.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.64,1:48:14.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,也不要高兴得太早\N{\rENG}I wouldn't go overboard.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:15.10,1:48:18.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,最好不要出国\N{\rENG}In fact, I wouldn't leave the state,
Dialogue: 0,1:48:18.73,1:48:21.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,不要开始购物\N{\rENG}or start buying new stuff or chartering
Dialogue: 0,1:48:21.44,1:48:23.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 或包机  - 我要从前台溜出去\N{\rENG}- any more jets.  - I gotta sneak by the guy
Dialogue: 0,1:48:23.07,1:48:24.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,因为我没钱支付酒店的帐单\N{\rENG}at the front desk 'cause I can't pay the hotel bill.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:24.95,1:48:27.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,这些事不能说给我听\N{\rENG}I can't be a party to that information.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.91,1:48:31.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,祝你好运 威尔斯先生\N{\rENG}Good luck, Mr. Wells.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:31.29,1:48:34.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我们还会注意你的\N{\rENG}We'll be keeping an eye on you.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.75,1:48:42.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你下一步怎么办\N{\rENG}What are you gonna do now, Wells?
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.34,1:50:04.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨 肯尼\N{\rENG}Hey, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.96,1:50:06.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,我仍然担心桑树\N{\rENG}I-I'm still worried about that mulberry
Dialogue: 0,1:50:06.59,1:50:08.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 伸到我家院子里  - 我知道 哈特\N{\rENG}- over the back fence.  - Yeah. I know, Hart.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.13,1:50:10.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你\N{\rENG}It's good to see you.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:10.93,1:50:12.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,很高兴见到你 肯尼\N{\rENG}Good to see you, too, Kenny.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.50,1:50:45.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我能进来吗\N{\rENG}Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.54,1:51:24.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 喝咖啡吗  - 好的\N{\rENG}- You want coffee?  - Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.92,1:51:32.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,这房子很漂亮\N{\rENG}This place looks great.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:35.80,1:51:38.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,你也一样 凯\N{\rENG}So do you, Kay.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:42.69,1:51:44.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我做的窗帘\N{\rENG}I made curtains.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:44.44,1:51:47.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,用那块布做的\N{\rENG}From that fabric.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:47.19,1:51:48.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rENG}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.74,1:51:54.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,有一些你的邮件\N{\rENG}Some stuff came for you, some mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.41,1:52:44.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\rENG}What?
Dialogue: 0,1:52:44.91,1:52:47.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,是什么\N{\rENG}What is it?


